{
  "texts": [
    "In this case, optimal performance (86,75 percent) is attained when employing the embedding model tailored for BPMN terminology, namely bert-finetuned-bpmn 11.",
    "Conversely, for the BPMN process model, superior results (91,57 percent) are achieved by leveraging the all-MiniLM-L6-v2 model.",
    "It is worth noticing that such results surpass even the performance of the BPLLM pipeline relying on the natural language representation for the same business process.",
    "Additionally, we evaluated the paraphrase-xlm-r-multilingual-v1foot_11 model, which maps sentences to a 768-dimensional dense vector space.",
    "However, we did not observe any significant improvements in the accuracy of our BPLLM pipeline.Based on the obtained results, we generated t-SNE charts for the most effective combinations, as depicted in Figure 7."
  ]
}